    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Related, but different. pdb runs in the same process, and we do know when it's expecting input. I think it  needs someone to do the work so that when the HTML input box is removed in the frontend, a message is sent back to the kernel which will raise `EOFError`.\r\n\r\nThat may need a new message type, or we could do it as a metadata field on the existing stdin reply message."
